issue.body:
Bumps [react-hook-form](https://github.com/react-hook-form/react-hook-form) from 7.7.0 to 7.10.0.
Release notes

Sourced from react-hook-form's releases.

Version 7.10.0

üçå deprecated defaultValue at useFieldArray as a required prop (#5636)

function Test() {
  const { control, register } = useForm();
  const { fields, append, prepend, remove, swap, move, insert } = useFieldArray({
    control,
    name: "test",
  });

return (
{fields.map((field, index) => (
<input
key={field.id} // important to include key with field's id
{...register(test.${index}.value)}


    

  • 

       defaultValue={field.value} // no longer required
/>

    
))}
);
}

üë®üèª‚Äçüíª fix #5787 controller type for defaultValue (#5792) üòø fix #5777 regression on unmount defaultValue with shouldUnregister:true (#5778) üìÖ close #5724 setValue skip parse date time as object (#5729) üéÆ #5712 enable controller with native validation (#5716) üêõ fix spread non-primitive values in nested array fields (#5705) üé™ batch single watch update (#5707) üèüÔ∏è batch unregister inputs (#5706) üêû fix #5699 trigger not focusing first input with error (#5700)

Version 7.9.0

ü•á feature: support browser native form control (#5503)

export default function App() {
  const { register, handleSubmit } = useForm({
    shouldUseNativeValidation: true,
  });
  const onSubmit = (data) => console.log(data);

return (
<form onSubmit={handleSubmit(onSubmit)}>
<input
{...register("firstName", {
required: "This is required from bill."
})}
</tr></table>

... (truncated)

Changelog

Sourced from react-hook-form's changelog.

[7.10.0] - 2021-07-02

Changed

  • defaultValue is no longer a required prop for register input with useFieldArray

[7.9.0] - 2021-06-19

Add

  • new config at useForm to enabled native browser validation
const { register, handleSubmit } = useForm({
  shouldUseNativeValidation: true,
});

[7.8.5] - 2021-06-15

Change

  • useController no longer access input ref except focus event for focus management

[7.8.0] - 2021-06-5

Added

  • setValue support shouldTouch to update formState touchFields
setValue('firstName', 'value', { shouldTouch: true });
  • register now accept value as option
register('firstName', { value: 'value' });

Changed

  • isValid will initialise as false

[7.7.1] - 2021-05-30

Fixed

  • shouldUnregister: false should not shallow merge or register absent input fields from defaultValues

  • 4494e2e üçå deprecated defaultValue at useFieldArray as required prop (#5636)
  • 51eaf49 üìÖ close #5724 setValue skip parse date time as object (#5729)
  • 6e577f9 üéÆ #5712 enable controller with native validation (#5716)
  • 4914c41 üêõ fix spread non-primitive values in nested array fields (#5705)
  • 49f039e üé™ batch single watch update (#5707)
  • 00c89d8 üèüÔ∏è batch unregister inputs (#5706)

body: can you please provide an isolated codesandbox?

This one [https://codesandbox.io/s/keen-shamir-2zqxn](https://codesandbox.io/s/keen-shamir-2zqxn)  
Do you need that I change something?

@leosuncin  I think it's not caused because Date is nullable,
but because Date is not an primitive type but an `class`, so an field with property of type `File` will show the same error message

> @leosuncin I think it's not caused because Date is nullable,
> but because Date is not an primitive type but an `class`, so an field with property of type `File` will show the same error message

I don't think so, the error is a `FieldError` as you can see in the image

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4307697/124483243-56a5ab80-dd67-11eb-96c3-e7acecda449c.png)

The problem is how typescript infer the type, here https://github.com/react-hook-form/react-hook-form/blob/90e3332a7efeda8c4e40519f7957671fb905ec3a/src/types/utils.ts#L35-L51

@bluebill1049, I updated the codesanbox to show more info, I hope it helps
I would remove that `| null` for now.
